---
const stats = [
  { value: '5+', label: 'Years Experience' },
  { value: '50+', label: 'APIs Built' },
  { value: '15+', label: 'Projects Delivered' },
];
---

<div id="about" class="space-y-8">
  <!-- Section label -->
  <div class="reveal-up">
    <span class="heading-section accent-line">About</span>
  </div>

  <!-- Heading -->
  <h2 class="reveal-up reveal-delay-1 heading-lg">
    Engineering reliable<br/>systems at scale
  </h2>

  <!-- Body -->
  <p class="reveal-up reveal-delay-2 text-lg text-[var(--muted)] leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
    I'm a backend developer based in Indonesia, focused on building reliable
    and performant server-side applications. My experience spans enterprise
    travel platforms, national government systems, and fintech infrastructure
    â€” always with an emphasis on clean API design, data integrity, and
    maintainable code.
  </p>
  <p class="reveal-up reveal-delay-3 text-lg text-[var(--muted)] leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
    I believe in writing code that's easy to reason about, test, and extend.
    When I'm not coding, I enjoy mentoring junior developers and exploring
    new approaches to system design.
  </p>

  <!-- Stats strip -->
  <div class="reveal-up reveal-delay-4 flex gap-8 pt-8 border-t border-[var(--border)]">
    {stats.map((stat) => (
      <div>
        <div class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-extrabold text-[var(--color-accent)] font-display">
          {stat.value}
        </div>
        <div class="font-mono text-xs text-[var(--muted)] uppercase tracking-widest mt-1">
          {stat.label}
        </div>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>
</div>
